bomb the damn building...

950
01:11:39,781 --> 01:11:43,057
and now the job
that was not supposed to look like a job's

951
01:11:43,141 --> 01:11:45,370
beginning to look very much

952
01:11:45,460 --> 01:11:47,416
like a job.

953
01:11:56,019 --> 01:11:57,975
All right. Fuck it.

954
01:12:00,499 --> 01:12:02,455
If the Rabbi wants a war...

955
01:12:03,339 --> 01:12:05,806
...l'll give him a war.

956
01:12:12,818 --> 01:12:14,570
Saul.

957
01:12:17,178 --> 01:12:19,567
- Saul.

958
01:12:20,018 --> 01:12:22,213
<i>Saul, the phone's been...</i>

959
01:12:22,297 --> 01:12:24,254
Oh.

960
01:12:24,337 --> 01:12:26,293
I thought you were Saul.

961
01:12:28,897 --> 01:12:31,127
People have been thinking I'm somebody else.

962
01:12:34,577 --> 01:12:37,010
Your predicament reminds me of a story.

963
01:12:37,096 --> 01:12:39,451
Hitchcock. North By Northwest.

964
01:12:40,295 --> 01:12:44,049
The movie where everybody thinks Cary Grant
is a man named George Kaplan,

965
01:12:44,135 --> 01:12:47,128
but the thing is there is no George Kaplan.
It's just a made-up name.

966
01:12:47,215 --> 01:12:49,570
But names, even made-up ones...

967
01:12:52,015 --> 01:12:54,245
...can bring about quite a bit of trouble.

968
01:12:56,174 --> 01:12:57,574
Now...

969
01:12:57,654 --> 01:12:59,804
the woman in the picture with Grant,

970
01:12:59,894 --> 01:13:02,249
- <i>her name was er...</i>
- Eva Marie Saint.

971
01:13:02,334 --> 01:13:05,087
- Oh... you know this movie.
- I know this movie.

972
01:13:05,174 --> 01:13:08,246
I took my father to see it in 1959.
His English wasn't very good,

973
01:13:08,334 --> 01:13:11,166
but boy, did he like Miss Saint.

974
01:13:11,253 --> 01:13:14,051
After the movie he turned to me and he said,
"She's a real Buick."

975
01:13:14,133 --> 01:13:17,523
You see, he couldn't pronounce
the word beauty, so he'd say Buick.

976
01:13:18,812 --> 01:13:22,566
- Caused quite a bit of confusion.
- Using the wrong name'll do that.

977
01:13:26,772 --> 01:13:28,603
Is that my money?

978
01:13:28,692 --> 01:13:30,045
This is everything I owe you.

979
01:14:03,289 --> 01:14:07,077
It's the Sabbath. You see,
we don't answer the phone on the Sabbath.

980
01:14:07,169 --> 01:14:08,965
I know.

981
01:14:09,049 --> 01:14:10,845
Normally Saul turns off the ringer.

982
01:14:10,929 --> 01:14:12,078
Saul!

983
01:14:12,169 --> 01:14:14,728
I tell you, you can't find good help these days.

984
01:14:18,567 --> 01:14:20,763
Saul's dead.

985
01:14:23,447 --> 01:14:24,675
<i>They're all dead.</i>

986
01:14:48,165 --> 01:14:50,122
Oh, I've been in this room before.

987
01:14:52,565 --> 01:14:54,521
Looks the same as it did 20 years ago.

988
01:14:55,765 --> 01:14:57,720
Somehow...

989
01:14:58,564 --> 01:14:59,917
Somehow it seems different.

990
01:15:00,005 --> 01:15:03,633
The way your car seems different
when someone else is driving it.

991
01:15:04,884 --> 01:15:07,921
Then again, it's been 20 years
since I've been in a car.

992
01:15:09,163 --> 01:15:12,201
Two decades spent behind three inches
of bulletproof glass

993
01:15:12,283 --> 01:15:16,879
due to a natural fear of high-powered rifles
and quiet... rooftops in New Jersey.

994
01:15:16,963 --> 01:15:18,919
20 years...

995
01:15:20,843 --> 01:15:24,119
...locked away in my own paranoia,
a prisoner in my own home.

996
01:15:26,522 --> 01:15:29,275
Only to be delivered to fate by a boy.

997
01:15:32,881 --> 01:15:37,033
<i>Well, Anthony, it looks as though you've won,</i>
<i>if such a term may be applied.</i>

998
01:15:39,361 --> 01:15:41,636
<i>If I were wearing a hat, I would take it off.</i>

999
01:15:45,561 --> 01:15:47,118
Should we get on with it, then?

1000
01:15:53,400 --> 01:15:55,356
You can keep your hat on, Schlomo.

1001
01:16:00,320 --> 01:16:03,595
Looks like we were sold a bill of goods
by the same salesman.

1002
01:16:06,079 --> 01:16:08,035
Nice speech, though.

1003
01:16:11,758 --> 01:16:13,988
I wish I was standing for it.

1004
01:16:24,598 --> 01:16:26,747
You... you brought this upon our heads.

1005
01:16:29,037 --> 01:16:32,996
- Me?
- You... you hired Good Kat to kill my son.

1006
01:16:34,877 --> 01:16:36,832
After you murdered my son?

1007
01:16:38,557 --> 01:16:41,309
- I had no hand in that.
- Oh, sure.

1008
01:16:41,396 --> 01:16:43,352
Just like in '84?

1009
01:16:43,876 --> 01:16:47,312
I suppose you had no hand in that either.
Just a finger, maybe?

1010
01:16:49,956 --> 01:16:51,911
Time's up, Rabbi.

1011
01:16:53,475 --> 01:16:56,307
Lying to a dead man's
the same as lying to yourself.

1012
01:17:00,154 --> 01:17:02,111
You were getting too big.

1013
01:17:03,914 --> 01:17:05,870
See...

1014
01:17:07,114 --> 01:17:09,150
...problem when two men are standing in a room

1015
01:17:09,233 --> 01:17:12,032
is you can only look at one of them
and they were looking at you

1016
01:17:12,113 --> 01:17:15,469
with their backs turned,
their shirt collars smiling at me.

1017
01:17:18,033 --> 01:17:19,386
Then they called you The Boss.

1018
01:17:22,353 --> 01:17:24,308
It was clear what had to be done.

1019
01:17:30,552 --> 01:17:33,271
Try and appreciate how it feels, Schlomo...

1020
01:17:35,671 --> 01:17:39,425
...to wake up in the middle of the night
with six bullets burning in your stomach.

1021
01:17:40,271 --> 01:17:42,501
Lying in a pool of your own blood and shit.

1022
01:17:46,711 --> 01:17:48,666
The dead eyes of...

1023
01:17:51,990 --> 01:17:54,504
...of your wife... staring back at you.

1024
01:17:58,150 --> 01:18:00,106
The only thing keeping you from passing out

1025
01:18:00,190 --> 01:18:03,148
is the sound of the footsteps of the man
going down the hall...

1026
01:18:04,510 --> 01:18:06,465
...looking for your son.

1027
01:18:11,468 --> 01:18:13,425
I managed to save my son, Schlomo.

1028
01:18:15,069 --> 01:18:17,024
And now...

1029
01:18:18,148 --> 01:18:20,184
...after all these years...

1030
01:18:22,027 --> 01:18:23,506
...in spite of our agreement!

1031
01:18:24,747 --> 01:18:26,306
You... you...

1032
01:18:26,387 --> 01:18:29,265
fucking backstabbing Philistine.

1033
01:18:30,148 --> 01:18:32,217
You managed to take my son away from me.

1034
01:18:33,707 --> 01:18:35,663
Well...

1035
01:18:36,867 --> 01:18:38,903
...now I've taken your son away from you.

1036
01:18:38,986 --> 01:18:41,898
I told you I had nothing to do with...

1037
01:18:50,706 --> 01:18:52,536
You haven't heard.

1038
01:18:52,625 --> 01:18:54,581
Will I?

1039
01:18:55,145 --> 01:18:58,693
Look at my face, Schlomo. Look at my smile.

1040
01:19:00,544 --> 01:19:02,182
Your son is dead.

1041
01:19:05,424 --> 01:19:07,493
Your son is dead.

1042
01:19:10,064 --> 01:19:12,577
I'm gonna kill you. Hm.

1043
01:19:14,823 --> 01:19:15,892
SLEVIN: <i>Rabbi.</i>

1044
01:19:17,143 --> 01:19:19,134
<i>Are you familiar with the Shmoo?</i>

1045
01:19:30,982 --> 01:19:32,938
Fisher.

1046
01:19:34,742 --> 01:19:36,697
Fisher, listen to me.

1047
01:19:39,421 --> 01:19:41,889
I already told you,

1048
01:19:41,982 --> 01:19:43,937
I'm not Nick Fisher.

1049
01:19:49,060 --> 01:19:51,017
Then who is Nick Fisher?

1050
01:19:57,260 --> 01:19:59,137
I think you mean, who was Nick Fisher?

1051
01:20:00,739 --> 01:20:02,537
Fisher was the answer to a question.

1052
01:20:02,619 --> 01:20:05,258
How do you get to two men
that can't be gotten to?

1053
01:20:12,898 --> 01:20:14,855
<i>You get them to come to you.</i>

1054
01:20:22,537 --> 01:20:24,971
<i>But to do that... I needed a name.</i>

1055
01:20:25,777 --> 01:20:27,848
<i>And where do you find names?</i>

1056
01:20:27,938 --> 01:20:29,928
<i>In books.</i>

1057
01:20:34,137 --> 01:20:35,649
<i>And who has books?</i>

1058
01:20:43,416 --> 01:20:45,372
<i>Well, your bookies have books.</i>

1059
01:20:47,136 --> 01:20:48,250
He's clean.

1060
01:20:48,336 --> 01:20:50,291
SLEVIN: <i>Crooked bookies...</i>

1061
01:20:51,096 --> 01:20:54,053
- <i>... who work with big-time crooks.</i>
- So... why are you here?

1062
01:21:05,254 --> 01:21:06,927
<i>I was looking for a gambler.</i>

1063
01:21:08,494 --> 01:21:10,166
<i>One who was in both books...</i>

1064
01:21:10,894 --> 01:21:13,169
<i>... with a lot of red in the minus column.</i>

1065
01:21:13,253 --> 01:21:14,369
Got him.

1066
01:21:14,453 --> 01:21:16,410
<i>And that's when I found Nick Fisher.</i>

1067
01:21:17,013 --> 01:21:19,049
<i>A lowlife that no-one was gonna miss.</i>

1068
01:21:20,693 --> 01:21:22,012
1729.

1069
01:21:22,093 --> 01:21:24,243
Nick Fisher.

1070
01:21:24,332 --> 01:21:26,289
OK.

1071
01:21:37,531 --> 01:21:39,487
GOODKAT: <i>There was a time.</i>

1072
01:21:55,530 --> 01:21:58,043
All that was left to do was make the phone ring.

1073
01:22:17,768 --> 01:22:21,363
<i>All I had to do was pull the trigger</i>
<i>and wait for you to call the man</i>

1074
01:22:21,448 --> 01:22:23,678
<i>who does the jobs that no-one else wants.</i>

1075
01:22:25,728 --> 01:22:27,684
THE BOSS: <i>I want an outsider brought in.</i>

1076
01:22:29,088 --> 01:22:31,203
There's a specialist.

1077
01:22:33,326 --> 01:22:35,317
Calls himself Mr. Good Kat.

1078
01:22:41,126 --> 01:22:43,082
Fine.

1079
01:22:44,726 --> 01:22:46,876
Tell him he can expect me in the morning.

1080
01:22:51,365 --> 01:22:53,322
Are you ready?

1081
01:22:53,405 --> 01:22:55,361
Yeah.

1082
01:22:58,325 --> 01:23:00,280
It's just that one last thing.

1083
01:23:08,884 --> 01:23:10,237
THE BOSS: <i>Mr. Good Kat.</i>

1084
01:23:11,204 --> 01:23:12,842
It's been a long time.

1085
01:23:17,003 --> 01:23:21,474
I'm sorry to have kept you waiting, Mr. Good Kat.
So I'll get right down to business.

1086
01:23:22,563 --> 01:23:26,271
Slim Hopkins, the man who ran my book,
was hit yesterday.

1087
01:23:27,923 --> 01:23:30,072
And I guess you've already heard about...

1088
01:23:31,522 --> 01:23:34,036
- <i>... my son.</i>
- Yes, I heard.

1089
01:23:35,001 --> 01:23:36,754
I need you to sort it out for me.

1090
01:23:36,842 --> 01:23:38,480
Who's the mark?

1091
01:23:38,561 --> 01:23:40,075
Yitzchok.

1092
01:23:43,321 --> 01:23:44,880
Yitzchok, The Rabbi's son?

1093
01:23:44,961 --> 01:23:47,077
<i>You remember The Rabbi?</i>

1094
01:23:47,161 --> 01:23:48,912
I remember The Rabbi well.

1095
01:23:49,001 --> 01:23:50,559
<i>Thing is...</i>

1096
01:23:50,640 --> 01:23:53,075
it can't look like a job.

1097
01:23:53,961 --> 01:23:56,394
<i>If Yitzchok gets hit, The Rabbi will go to war.</i>

1098
01:23:58,880 --> 01:24:03,112
So... I need you to make it look like
it ain't what it is.

1099
01:24:04,599 --> 01:24:06,715
<i>Can that be done?</i>

1100
01:24:06,799 --> 01:24:08,710
Anything can be done.

1101
01:24:10,879 --> 01:24:13,154
Good. How?

1102
01:24:13,238 --> 01:24:15,309
Kansas City Shuffle.

1103
01:24:17,038 --> 01:24:18,915
I'm not familiar with the term.

1104
01:24:21,598 --> 01:24:23,668
I'll need to see Slim's books.

1105
01:24:23,758 --> 01:24:29,115
Slim's books were taken when he was hit,
but... I do keep copies.

1106
01:24:33,677 --> 01:24:35,793
What are you looking for?

1107
01:24:39,117 --> 01:24:41,677
This is our guy. Nick - 1729.

1108
01:24:42,316 --> 01:24:44,352
1729.

1109
01:24:44,436 --> 01:24:45,789
Nick Fisher.

1110
01:24:45,876 --> 01:24:46,945
Why him?

1111
01:24:48,036 --> 01:24:49,628
A loser.

1112
01:24:49,715 --> 01:24:51,911
Pick him up. Bring him here.

1113
01:25:00,115 --> 01:25:02,390
GOODKAT: <i>Still not talking to each other, huh?</i>

1114
01:25:02,474 --> 01:25:04,431
<i>Can't say that I blame you.</i>

1115
01:25:04,514 --> 01:25:06,584
- Why are you here?
- Big job.

1116
01:25:06,674 --> 01:25:09,632
I was under the impression
you no longer worked New York.

1117
01:25:09,714 --> 01:25:12,751
Like I said... very big job.

1118
01:25:12,834 --> 01:25:16,873
And you thought, as long as you're in town,
you'd drop by and see your old pal Schlomo,

1119
01:25:16,953 --> 01:25:19,626
and say, "Hello. How about them Yanks?"

1120
01:25:21,913 --> 01:25:23,869
No. But something like that.

1121
01:25:27,873 --> 01:25:30,706
Only problem is you and I aren't old friends.

1122
01:25:30,792 --> 01:25:32,225
And I hate baseball.

1123
01:25:32,312 --> 01:25:35,463
And since we're not friends and
you hate baseball, why the fuck are you here?

1124
01:25:35,552 --> 01:25:38,305
It's because we're not friends that I'm here.

1125
01:25:39,191 --> 01:25:42,787
Because if we had been friends,
I wouldn't have been hired to kill your son.

1126
01:25:42,871 --> 01:25:47,422
Because that is right at the top of my list
of things that friends do not do to their friends.

1127
01:25:47,511 --> 01:25:50,628
The good news for you is,
my friendship is for sale.

1128
01:25:51,390 --> 01:25:54,621
You see, it seems to me
that your son means more to you alive

1129
01:25:54,711 --> 01:25:56,621
than he does to The Boss dead.

1130
01:25:56,710 --> 01:25:58,860
And more money means more to me
than less money.

1131
01:25:58,950 --> 01:26:02,908
And you are the guy that sleeps with
all that green under your mattress.

1132
01:26:03,709 --> 01:26:05,223
I'm listening.

1133
01:26:05,310 --> 01:26:09,222
You will pay me double to kill The Boss
what The Boss was paying me to kill Yitzchok.

1134
01:26:09,309 --> 01:26:12,381
- Ohh.
- And that...

1135
01:26:14,109 --> 01:26:16,064
And that will make us friends.

1136
01:26:16,829 --> 01:26:18,784
Right, Rabbi?

1137
01:26:19,829 --> 01:26:21,147
Hm?

1138
01:26:25,108 --> 01:26:29,659
And... since friends do favors for their friends,
you will do a favor for me.

1139
01:26:29,747 --> 01:26:32,546
Pray tell? What is this favor?

1140
01:26:32,627 --> 01:26:36,017
Concerns a matter of debt collection.
One debt in particular.

1141
01:26:36,107 --> 01:26:37,222
Whose?

1142
01:26:37,307 --> 01:26:40,298
A flop. From Benny's book.
Goes by the name of Nick Fisher.

1143
01:26:40,387 --> 01:26:42,456
Who is he?

1144
01:26:42,546 --> 01:26:44,502
Just a loser.

1145
01:26:44,586 --> 01:26:46,542
You just made a lot of money.

1146
01:26:49,866 --> 01:26:52,938
SLEVIN: <i>And then I was free</i>
<i>to come and go as I pleased.</i>

1147
01:27:06,305 --> 01:27:07,101
Hm?

1148
01:27:07,184 --> 01:27:10,142
Whatever they're paying you...

1149
01:27:16,704 --> 01:27:18,057
Oh.

1150
01:27:18,943 --> 01:27:20,137
There is nobody.

1151
01:27:22,383 --> 01:27:24,339
I did this to you.

1152
01:27:27,222 --> 01:27:28,371
- Me.
- You.

1153
01:27:29,102 --> 01:27:30,821
Me.

1154
01:27:36,702 --> 01:27:38,658
Who are you?

1155
01:27:41,221 --> 01:27:43,133
BRIKOWSKl: <i>Who is he?</i>

1156
01:27:43,221 --> 01:27:47,373
Considering he no longer has fingerprints,
I'd say it's unlikely we'll ever know.

1157
01:27:47,461 --> 01:27:49,213
What about dental records?

1158
01:27:49,300 --> 01:27:54,659
Sure, find the bottom half of the jaw, then all
we need to do is find out who the dentist was.

1159
01:27:55,460 --> 01:27:57,416
What a fucking mess.

1160
01:27:58,740 --> 01:28:01,015
<i>Hey, Brikowski, it's Marty, you there?</i>

1161
01:28:01,100 --> 01:28:05,012
<i>We found two more bodies</i>
<i>to go along with the two you've already got.</i>

1162
01:28:05,100 --> 01:28:07,055
All right, I'll be right over.

1163
01:28:07,140 --> 01:28:11,291
Did you ever get a hold of The Rabbi so he can
get down here and identify what's left of his kid?

1164
01:28:11,379 --> 01:28:14,610
<i>Negative.</i>
<i>We've been calling for the last hour, no answer.</i>

1165
01:28:14,699 --> 01:28:16,132
Send somebody over.

1166
01:28:16,219 --> 01:28:17,368
<i>Copy.</i>

1167
01:28:19,298 --> 01:28:22,017
You all right? You look a little shook-up.

1168
01:28:22,098 --> 01:28:23,895
No, I'm fine.

1169
01:28:23,978 --> 01:28:25,934
All right.

1170
01:28:48,416 --> 01:28:51,487
- Yeah.
- <i>Hey, Brikowski, it's Murphy.</i>

1171
01:28:51,576 --> 01:28:53,089
Hey, Murph, what's up?

1172
01:28:53,175 --> 01:28:56,168
<i>Harry Kello came by today.</i>
<i>You remember Harry?</i>

1173
01:28:56,256 --> 01:28:59,964
He retired a few years ago. His wife just died,
so he comes in a couple of times a week,

1174
01:29:00,055 --> 01:29:02,011
talks shop, tells stories to the rooks.

1175
01:29:02,094 --> 01:29:05,644
Starts every sentence with, "The way
things used to be". Guy living in the past.

1176
01:29:05,735 --> 01:29:08,203
- Yeah. Yeah, what about him?
- <i>We're making small talk.</i>

1177
01:29:08,295 --> 01:29:11,764
Guy says he can't complain,
then all he does is fuckin' complain.

1178
01:29:11,854 --> 01:29:15,130
His dead wife, the leg he got shot in,
his crappy pension,

1179
01:29:15,214 --> 01:29:18,763
but then he stops when he sees the picture
Marty snapped of your kid.

1180
01:29:18,854 --> 01:29:22,528
Just stares at it.
I say, "What is it? You know the kid?"

1181
01:29:22,613 --> 01:29:25,252
Thing is, he ain't looking at the picture,
but at the name.

1182
01:29:25,333 --> 01:29:28,609
I've got it written at the bottom.
He knows that name: Slevin.

1183
01:29:47,851 --> 01:29:49,807
I have that same phone.

1184
01:30:01,770 --> 01:30:05,967
<i>About an hour later the phone rings, it's Harry,</i>
<i>talking like a goddamned machine gun,</i>

1185
01:30:06,050 --> 01:30:08,438
going on and on about a horse race back in '79.

1186
01:30:11,210 --> 01:30:13,165
<i>Aqueduct.</i>

1187
